:1. Natural language already has structure
Example: "I walked the dog";
note right
Page 1 witness:
- "I" = subject / agent
- "walked" = predicate / action
- "dog" = object / patient
- cat / rat = nearby object-type fillers

The first move is role binding, not ontology lookup.
end note

:2. Predicate roles imply soft typing
subject / predicate / object / typed participant;
note right
Roles create slots.
Slots imply acceptable fillers.
Acceptable fillers create soft type pressure.
end note

:3. Soft typing creates pressure
where explicit ontology is too weak;
note right
Pages 2-5:
- Wikidata assertions are useful but incomplete
- domain pressure asks for stricter semantics
- some needed constraints do not exist explicitly
- strict typing is a local result, not the starting point
end note

:4. Finland / UMK / Eurovision exposes layer collapse
selection competition != national participation;
note right
Clean 2025 pattern:
- Q126165306 = Uuden Musiikin Kilpailu 2025
- instance of UMK edition
- part of series: Uuden Musiikin Kilpailu
- part of: Finland in Eurovision 2025

Collapsed 2013 pattern:
- Q2226274 = Finland in Eurovision 2013
- aliases/description carry UMK2013 / UMK13
- typing and series mix national participation
  with selection competition edition

Latent split:
UMK 2013 -> selects/supports/is part of
Finland's Eurovision 2013 participation.
end note

:5. Q27968055 exposes order/type pathology
recurring event edition? event? metaclass? second-order class?;
note right
Q27968055 witness:
- current P279 includes Q1656682 event
  and Q3331189 version/edition/translation
- nearby diagnostic surface:
  P31 / P279 / P1269 / P2738 / P11260 / P8225
- pressure is about order:
  edition, event, metaclass, second-order class
- safer posture:
  underspecify via Q24017414
  rather than keep wrong superclass
end note

:6. Wikidata is too large and flat for direct global repair
extract latent residual structure instead;
note right
Pages 3-5 architecture:
Wikidata ontology
-> latent structure
-> residual
-> feature
-> constraint
-> domain projector
-> reviewable signal

The system does not globally solve Wikidata.
It projects bounded repair surfaces.
end note

:7. PNF / ITIR becomes the typed predicate carrier
roles + qualifiers + provenance + graph alignment;
note right
Pages 6-8:
- CAT -> mammal -> animal
- local graph reasoning over neighborhoods
- Wikipedia text + Wikidata graph -> PNF
- PNF -> typed graph
- corpus search becomes evidence
- "where did I talk about dogs?"
  can resolve through typed graph structure

PNF is the carrier for roles,
qualifiers, provenance, and residual state.
end note

:8. Corpus and multilingual divergence become evidence
English collapse vs Finnish distinction;
note right
Pages 8-10:
- canonical article hierarchy
- Simple Wiki / ordinary Wikipedia contrast
- pressure + signal + locus of control
- binary, conditional, functional, and floating signals
- machine translation proposes cross-language mappings
- multilingual consistency exposes hidden type distinctions
end note

:9. Domain projector emits bounded repair proposals
split / underspecify / remove bad superclass / hold;
note right
Outputs are not global truth claims.

They are bounded review signals:
- split collapsed entity
- underspecify instead of assert wrong superclass
- remove bad superclass
- hold for order review
- propose new relation or type
end note

:Abstract mechanism
weak text/graph claim -> predicate extraction
-> role binding -> soft type inference
-> ontology and corpus alignment
-> residual analysis -> constraint pressure
-> typed predicate envelope -> bounded proposal;
note right
General engine:
ITIR is a modular structural reasoning layer.
It converts language and weak graph data into typed,
provenance-bearing predicate envelopes, then checks
them against ontology, authority, domain constraints,
and corpus pressure before emitting review signals.
end note

